Update Submodules  **Command:**  <pre><code>git submodule update --init --recursive
</code></pre>   **What it does:** - Initializes and updates all git submodules - Ensures submodules are at correct commits - Required if project uses submodules  **Use when:** Working with projects that have git submodules.  Reset to Specific Commit  **Command:**  <pre><code>git reset --hard &lt;commit-hash&gt;
</code></pre>   **What it does:** - Resets repository to a specific commit - Discards all changes after that commit  **Use when:** Need to revert to a known good state.
